                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d661">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3982</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-03T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 20. In view of no vessel immediately available to send to Liberia,
                    British and French Governments have been asked to assist in affording Government
                    protection. When adequate protection has arrived in Liberian waters, you will be
                    instructed to join with British and French colleagues in advising Liberian
                    Government sever relations with Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
